data.description: Welcome to 118 Sprucedale Dr, Waterbury, CT 06706, nestled in the East End of Waterbury. This colonial-style home, constructed in 1983, offers 1906 sq ft of living space on a modest 8,712 sq ft (0.20 acre) lot. Boasting 3 bedrooms and 8 rooms in total, including a formal dining room, and living room with a cozy fireplace, an entertainment room and bonus den/4th bedroom/office, it provides ample space for comfortable living. With one full and one-half baths, a 2-car garage underneath, and a sliding door in the eat-in kitchen leading to a deck with serene views of the East End of Waterbury, this home offers both convenience and charm. Connected to public utilities (water and sewer) and featuring a baseboard hot water system fueled by an oil-fired furnace, supplemented by an electric hot water heater, this property ensures practicality and ease of maintenance. Adorned with low maintenance vinyl siding, this home presents an appealing blend of functionality and modest elegance. Schedule a viewing today to discover the understated beauty of this conveniently located property.
